OL,3,CDrug producer jailed after property
OL,4,C'significantly hotter than neighbours'
OL,6,F"As is typical in these case, the
OL,7,Felectrical supply in this property had
OL,8,Fbeen illegally bypassed and the
OL,9,Foutlets within were dangerously
OL,10,Foverloaded.
OL,12,F"When combined with the huge quantity
OL,13,Fof flammable material inside the
OL,14,Faddress, these illegal modifications
OL,15,Fcould easily have caused a very
OL,16,Fserious fire.
OL,18,F"That's why we urge local residents to
OL,19,Ftell us about properties they believe
OL,20,Fare being used in this way as soon as
OL,21,Fpossible."
